   "source": [
    "All variables are positively correlated with life expectancy, with the strongest correlation observed for GDP (r=0.76) followed by calorie supply (r=0.73). Calorie supply is also strongly correlated with GDP (r=0.69), suggesting that these variables may capture overlapping aspects of economic development and living standards. As a result, including both variables in the same regression model may introduce multicollinearity, reducing the ability to distinguish their independent effects on life expectancy. In contrast, vegetable supply exhibits only a moderate correlation with GDP (r=0.39), indicating that it may provide additional information beyond income levels alone. These observations are largely consistent with the results obtained from the regression models presented in the next section.\n",
